msContents.summary: 279 letters and summaries, 228 are autograph letters of Cosimo III, son of Ferdinand II, to Alessandro da Verazano. Verazano seems to have been an envoy of Cosimo in Venice, but chiefly involved with affairs of the Holy Roman Empire rather than relations with the Republic of Venice. Verazano seems to have interleaved drafts or précis of his letters (49 items) with those received from Cosimo in response.

supportDesc.extent: 520 items : 287 x 202 to 330 x 225 mm. bound to 331 x 230 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 520; [1-520]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in various cursive scripts by multiple hands.

binding.p: Contemporary parchment. Some folios completely detached.

origin.p: Written mostly in Florence, with some in Venice, 1696-1703.
